body.description: Nuby’s Softees Pacifier & Teether is a multi-purpose product for comforting and soothing your little one. The soft pacifier helps calm your little one when they get fussy, while the textured handle doubles as a teether to provide relief to tender gums. With a soothing, comfortable sit, the all-silicone design is lightweight so your baby will have an easier time keeping it in their mouth, rather than dropping it on the floor. Nuby always keeps you and your family’s safety in mind. Nuby’s Softees Pacifier & Teether is made of 100% silicone, which is BPA-free and made to last.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice big handle for my baby's little hands
reviews.reviewText: My baby isn't a huge pacifier fan, but I've been trying different styles to see if we find one he loves. He's still not obsessed with these, but instead of immediately spitting them out he actually grabs the handle and holds it in his mouth - sometimes he still ends up pulling it out, but since he can control the pacifier himself he seems to like it more than others we have tried. i like that he can get his tiny 4 month old hands around the handle and I hope that these grow on him the more we offer them to him.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice silicone pacifiers for baby.
reviews.reviewText: I got these for our 5 month old since you can never have enough pacifiers it seems. The colors are pretty muted which seems like the current style and these Nuby Silicone Softees Pacifier & Teether, 5 pk, Neutral are made out of silicone which I really like. He latches on these pretty well, they are soft and they work great for him. Of course every baby is different so your results may differ but overall happy with these and would get again.On a side note, I find it funny we had a bunch of elaborate pacifiers on the market with our middle children and we now have come full circle back to the basic pacifier that is really similar to the standard one you likely got when your child was born. It is funny how that works.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Pacifiers For Teething Babies!!
reviews.reviewText: My baby preferred these pacifiers over the other 3 brands I had previously purchased for him. He was not taking any for the first few months. He is now four months old and currently teething. We gave these pacifiers a try and he absolutely loves them!! They help soothe his itchy gums and the handle makes it easy for him to hold. Easy to clean. They are super soft, all silicone which is perfect because I don’t have to worry about my baby hurting his gums. My baby is no longer fussy. Highly recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for teething
reviews.reviewText: I really like these silicone pacifiers/teethers. I think that one solid piece is a good idea for teething so it's less likely that parts will break off. My little one didn't really use them as straight pacifiers at a younger age but after a few months he started using them more as teethers and seems to really enjoy them, though he does still prefer his normal pacifiers when not trying to chew. The colors are cute, too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Value Pacifiers
reviews.reviewText: These are a great value for such a large set of pacifiers. They are good for both soothing and teething support. They can be thrown in the dishwasher and don't have any extra parts that can trap germs which is always a bonus. I also love that the handles are big enough for attaching a pacifier strap to them. Very happy with these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good price for Newborn Pacifiers
reviews.reviewText: This is a good deal for five pacifiers!I like these ones because first and foremost, my baby will take them! Also, I like that it is easy to attach a pacifier clip to these because the handle sticks out quite a bit. On some of the other pacifiers (like the Avent soothee), it can be hard to attach a clip and when you do, the cord is pressed up against the baby's face and can leave a mark. There is no problem of that with these pacifiers.I like that they are one piece and that water can't get trapped inside when cleaning them. They are very easy to clean and sterilize.There is a nice variety of colors in this set, including brights and more subdued colors. They are packaged in a "giftable" pouch.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love the idea of these and that their double sided for teething. However my lil guy won't take to them, I've yet to find a pacifier that he likes, so my search continues. Otherwise if your lil one isn't pucky, These are great and a high quality product!
